Mexico ' s TIIE 28 - day rate falls to 20 . 28 pct . Mexico ' s 28 - day interbank interest rate for Tuesday , July 22 , was fixed at 20 . 28 percent , down 12 basis points from 20 . 40 percent , the rate for July 21 , Banco de Mexico said Monday . The 28 - day TIIE is a market - weighted average interbank rate that is revised each working day . It is valid for the day after it is set . The new rate will be published in Tuesday ' s edition of the Mexican government ' s Official Gazette . The TIIE is a market - weighted average interbank rate that is replacing the TIIP , an average interbank rate . ( ( - - Mexico City Newsroom 525 728 - 9558 ) ) 
